properties.Name: MedicalInformationBureauReportImpairment
properties.Description:
The specific impairments reported on the associated MIB Report.

If a company finds that one of its applicants has a physical impairment or ailment listed by the MIB, the company is required to report the information to the MIB in the form of a code number.

Columns.Name: MibReportId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Medical Information Bureau Report.

Columns.Name: ImpairmentId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of an Impairment Code.

Columns.Name: ImpairmentReportedDate
Columns.Description: The date that the specific Impairment was reported.

Columns.Name: ImpairmentReportStatement
Columns.Description: A statement, comments or additional information regarding the reported Impairment.

Columns.Name: ExaminerId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of an Examiner.
